feat: canonical repo auto-detection with fork-aware upstream resolution

Rewrites the org/repo detection in `apx init` to parse git remote URLs
instead of relying on filesystem path heuristics, adds fork-aware upstream
detection for consumption workflows, and documents the fork workflow.

Changes:

- Parse `git remote get-url origin` for org/repo detection
  (SSH shorthand, SSH URL, HTTPS, git:// protocols) with regex matching.
  Falls back to GOPATH-style path inspection when git is unavailable.

- Run auto-detection in both interactive and non-interactive init flows
  so `--org`/`--repo` flags are only required when detection fails.

- Change default canonical repo name from `your-apis-repo` to `apis`
  across config, examples, docs, and tests (11 locations).

- Detect fork via `upstream` git remote: when origin and upstream point
  to different orgs, use the upstream org for all consumption paths
  (go_package, buf module, dependency resolution). Adds `UpstreamOrg`
  field to `ProjectDefaults` for downstream visibility.

- Add comprehensive unit tests for URL parsing, fork detection,
  and smart defaults (22 test cases in detector package).

- Add `docs/app-repos/working-with-forks.md` documenting what works on
  forks (all consumption/authoring), what doesn't (publish, tag, PR),
  and the recommended fork→PR→merge→CI-publish workflow.

- Add fork FAQ entry in `docs/troubleshooting/faq.md`.

- Fix duplicate `test-integration` target in Makefile.

- Fix misleading "Interactive mode doesn't work" heading in quickstart.md.
